<DOC><DOCNO> AP880509-0080 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-09-88 1246EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-EscapeeRecaptured     05-09 0163</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Escapee Recaptured,0165</SECOND><HEAD>Murderer Recaptured 10 Miles from Prison</HEAD><DATELINE>MOUNDSVILLE, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A murderer who escaped five weeks agowith two other inmates from a maximum-security prison wasrecaptured today about 10 miles from the prison, state police said.   Details of the arrest of Tommie Mollohan this morning were notimmediately available, a state police dispatcher said.   Mollohan, 45, had been sighted several times in the remote,wooded area of Marshall County since his escape April 3. The twoinmates who escaped with him from the West Virginia Pentitentiaryin Moundsville were recaptured last month.   Penitentiary officials had described Mollohan as the mastermindof the breakout. He was serving a life sentence without chance ofparole for the 1973 robbery and murder of a grocer. At the time,Mollohan had escaped from a Florida prison and also was wanted inGeorgia and North Carolina on armed robbery charges.   The other two escapees also were serving life sentences withoutchance of parole.</TEXT></DOC>